modules.description: Creates and manages a graphical interface with text inputs and radio options, and integrates with image display functionality. Works with interface type, strings, and functions for handling user input and image updates. Used to build interactive applications where user controls affect real-time image rendering.

Provides functions for creating and manipulating GTK+ widgets, including buttons, labels, and entry fields. Operates on types such as Gtk.widget, Gtk.button, and Gtk.entry from the lablgtk library. Enables construction of graphical user interfaces for applications requiring event-driven interactions.

Provides functions to create and manipulate GTK widgets that render MLpost graphics, including embedding and updating visual content. Works with Gtk.widget and MLpost picture data structures to display vector-based images. Used to integrate interactive visualizations into GTK-based applications.
